body.name: DaVinci Autumn 4-in-1 Convertible Crib in Chestnut, Greenguard Gold Certified
features: GREENGUARD GOLD CERTIFIED: This product has undergone rigorous scientific testing for over 10,000 chemical emissions and VOCs. It contributes to cleaner indoor air, creating a healthier environment for your baby to sleep, play, and grow

GROWS WITH BABY: Four adjustable mattress positions that can be lowered as your baby begins to sit and stand. Easily converts to toddler bed, daybed, and full-size bed (toddler conversion kit M3099 and full-size conversion kit M5789 sold separately)
QUALITY MATERIAL: Made of solid sustainable New Zealand pinewood and TSCA compliant engineered wood
FOR YOUR BABY'S SAFETY: Say goodbye to toxic chemicals. Finished in a non-toxic multi-step painting process and lead and phthalate safe
COMPLETE THE LOOK: Shop Autumn 4-Drawer Changer Dresser (M4355), Autumn Bookcase / Hutch (M4309) and Jayden 6-Drawer Double Wide Dresser (M5966) for a coordinated nursery
body.description: Our bestselling Autumn 4-in-1 Crib is designed to fit any nursery from traditional to contemporary with a high headboard, sturdy slats and refined molding. Combining traditional appeal with timeless clean lines, this GREENGUARD Gold Certified crib is constructed of 100% natural solid New Zealand pine wood. Offers easy conversion to a toddler bed, daybed and full-sized bed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This crib exceeded my expectations! Very study and durable. Absolutely love the color. Happy with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 1, 2014
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great looking crib
reviews.reviewText: My wife and I went shopping at numerous baby & furniture stores looking for the right crib. Unfortunately, there isn't a wide selection of grey cribs which is the style we were looking for.I actually ordered this crib directly through the manufacturers website, but received a call a couple days later saying it was out of stock and would take up to 2 months to ship. I cancelled the order once I saw Amazon had it available for shipping the next day.I was a little nervous about the crib as we had not seen it in person (only viewed it online) and I didn't know how difficult it would be to put together. Luckily, there was nothing to be concerned about. The crib showed up a few days after ordering and was very easy to put together (this coming from someone who is not very handy.) It feels sturdy and looks great in the nursery and we're looking forward to using it once our child is old enough for it.Overall, the quality is perfect for what we were looking for and the fact that it will convert into a toddler bed and later a bed is great.Keep in mind, this is not the same quality as top end cribs from furniture stores. The wood is a little softer, so I'm sure it will scratch and dent with use. But that is all about how much you want to spend. What we were looking for was a good looking, safe crib and this one meets both of those criteria.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 11, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Crib is more beautiful in person!
reviews.reviewText: LOVE LOVE LOVE this crib!!!!!!!!! I have a pink, grey and white nursery that is vintage themed. I was looking for a slate grey crib to match the paint job, and this matches so perfectly I have had people ask me if I painted the crib to match the wall! Not only is the color absolutely lovely, but the crib is beautiful. It's incredibly solid, doesn't move at all when you try to shake it or bend over it. I am so happy I went with this crib. My friend who is pregnant could not decide on a crib and after coming over and seeing mine she went and purchased the same one. Trust me, you will not regret this purchase. Such a great value too, you cannot go wrong with the price. It also is really easy to put together, took my husband and I less than an hour. I would buy again and again! And I cannot wait to convert this to a regular bed when my little angel grows up, it will make a beautiful headboard!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful but Could Be Improved Upon.
reviews.reviewText: First of all, this crib is beautiful. It’s an absolute pain to put together, but once it’s together it’s really beautiful. It’s pretty sturdy, but maybe a little lighter weight than I’d like (I’ll be buying some rubber or silicone stoppers for the feet because on wood floors it wants to move easily).While there is some adjustability in terms of height, the settings are only around 2 inches apart and the max height is still pretty low, though I’m sure this is probably a deliberate safety feature.Quality— while the wood finish is beautiful, it’s also VERY soft and we accidentally scratched it just assembling it. The other cosmetic thing I would change if I could is the fact that it’s assembled with large bolts and screws and they did not provide any kind of peg or cover to disguise the large drill holes once it’s put together. For such a lovely piece of furniture this little detail makes it look a little cheap.Overall, we’re very happy with it. The look is exactly what we wanted, and it was a great value for a 4-in-1 convertible crib.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This crib is beautiful. Haven’t tried to convert it to daybed or full size bed yet. It is perfect as a crib at this moment

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful gray crib
reviews.reviewText: I just received the crib today and was delivered a day early. Love the rich gray color and feels very sturdy. It came undamaged and all the parts were there. I put it together myself. It was fairly easy but definitely read/look at the diagram pictures careful. The panels are not marked A, B, D, E etc. Make sure you are using the correct sized screws. The one part I don't like is the Warning stickers on the side of the crib (don't judge ;) I will be taking that off. Rating it a 4 Star due to poor instructions and the warning sticker but rating the crib itself definitely a 5 star. All in all I love the crib and can't wait for our little one to arrive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So glad we picked this crib!
reviews.reviewText: This crib arrived in a large, flat cardboard box, and was super heavy. My husband was able to carry it upstairs to the nursery for assembly, but I would not have been able to do it myself, and I’m guessing he would have liked to have a second person helping him.The crib have LOTS of pieces, many of which looked similar. It took about an hour to put together, and overall, wasn’t too tough. We were happy with the quality; one piece was scratched pretty deep, though. We worked through the manufacturer’s website, and they shipped a replacement piece, no problem (we were pretty happy).Overall, the crib looks more expensive than what we paid, and we were happy that we selected this crib. It’s sturdy, not too tough to assemble, and doesn’t appear “cheap.” It does arrive in a very heavy box, so make sure you have help on hand if you’re trying to move up a staircase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 16, 2021
reviews.reviewText: My daughter puts this crib through hell. She jumps on it, slams into it, kicks it and chews on it. It is still holding up and in great condition. I’m shocked that it hasn’t crumbled. I also assembled by myself 9 months pregnant, so it is pretty easy to assemble! Great buy!
